<div id="review_4001454437" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4001454437" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/127815147-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610935970p2/127815147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4001454437?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/127815147-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4001454437" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1280836200746176122">The Langoliers started this book out in a beyond exceptional kind of way for me. I kept thinking I might eventually roll into a story that I was not as captivated with, but that was far from the case. Every novella in this book was an absolute ride with all the scary delights King is a master at creating for us. While I do normally tend to gravitate towards his longer stories, this collection showed me how King can create the same magic in a shorter amount of time. Easy 5/5 and one that I will b</span>
  <span id="freeText1280836200746176122" style="display:none">The Langoliers started this book out in a beyond exceptional kind of way for me. I kept thinking I might eventually roll into a story that I was not as captivated with, but that was far from the case. Every novella in this book was an absolute ride with all the scary delights King is a master at creating for us. While I do normally tend to gravitate towards his longer stories, this collection showed me how King can create the same magic in a shorter amount of time. Easy 5/5 and one that I will be sure to visit again.</span>
