<div id="review_550472722" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/550472722" />
    <a title="Jason Pellegrini" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5856788-jason-pellegrini"><img alt="Jason Pellegrini" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1476929194p2/5856788.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/550472722?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jason Pellegrini" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jason Pellegrini" href="/user/show/5856788-jason-pellegrini">Jason Pellegrini</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5856788-jason-pellegrini?shelf=audible">audible</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer550472722" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15421769604212000823"><br/>This was the last King collection of novellas I needed to read. You know that saying, ‘Save the best for last’? Well if this isn’t the best King novella collection, then it’s pretty damn close! King really found a groove here. I’d say it is some of his best storytelling. Let us visit each individual story before I give my overall rating. <br/><br/>The Langoliers - It can sometimes take a bit for a story to really keep my mind from wandering. This was not the case with ‘The Langoliers’. The concept was so </span>
  <span id="freeText15421769604212000823" style="display:none"><br />This was the last King collection of novellas I needed to read. You know that saying, ‘Save the best for last’? Well if this isn’t the best King novella collection, then it’s pretty damn close! King really found a groove here. I’d say it is some of his best storytelling. Let us visit each individual story before I give my overall rating. <br /><br />The Langoliers - It can sometimes take a bit for a story to really keep my mind from wandering. This was not the case with ‘The Langoliers’. The concept was so unique. Everything about this story screamed originality. This might be the most impressed I’ve been with King after having finished one of his stories<br />5/5<br /><br />Secret Garden, Secret Window - I had gone into this one having already been familiar with the movie. Another unique concept, but what was really impressive was how King was able to write Shooter and Mort. I won’t go too much into detail, but what King set off to do with these characters, he accomplished perfectly. <br />4/5<br /><br />The Library Policeman - Oh man! This story was something else. This was the story in the collection where I had to keep going. If it was a tv show, it would be LOST. You just had to continue on to the next section after one ended. It did drag at points and there was one extremely disturbing scene; one of those scenes that leave you saying maybe King had gone too far by writing it. Still, this was one powerhouse of a story.<br />4/5<br /><br />The Sun Dog - This was the weakest of the four stories. Took a long time to grab my attention. I kept finding myself spacing out and loosing track of what was going on. It did get somewhat interesting eventually, but then fizzled out. It just failed to get me to connect with the characters and the climax is a blur to me now. Some great Easter eggs, though, being a Castle Rock story!<br />3/5<br /><br />I can’t recommend this collection enough. It’s the only novella collection that gives ‘Different Seasons’ a run for its money. They should tell you how good it was!<br /><br />4.5/5<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15421769604212000823" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review550472722">
  <td colspan="2">
